# ğŸ§ª **Assignment â€“ AWS EBS Snapshot (Backup & Restore)**

### ğŸ”¹ **Step 1: Snapshot Create Karna (Backup Banana)**

```bash
aws ec2 create-snapshot \
--volume-id vol-0abc123def456... \
--description "CLI Snapshot Backup"
```

ğŸ§  Ye command tumhare EBS volume ka **snapshot (backup image)** banati hai.
Matlab agar kal ko data delete ya corrupt ho jaye, to isi snapshot se pura volume wapas restore kiya ja sakta hai.
Output mein tumhe `SnapshotId` milega (jaise `snap-0abc123xyz...`), use save kar lo.

---

### ğŸ”¹ **Step 2: Snapshot Se Naya Volume Banana (Restore Karna)**

```bash
aws ec2 create-volume \
--availability-zone us-east-1a \
--snapshot-id snap-0abc123xyz... \
--volume-type gp2
```

ğŸ§  Ye command tumhare snapshot se **ek naya EBS volume** create karti hai.
Isse tum apna purana data ya configuration **as it is** wapas le sakte ho â€” bilkul backup restore jesa.

---

### ğŸ”¹ **Step 3: Naye Volume Ko EC2 Pe Attach Karna**

```bash
aws ec2 attach-volume \
--volume-id vol-0new123def456... \
--instance-id i-0123abcdef4567gh \
--device /dev/xvdf
```

ğŸ§  Ab tum naya (restored) volume apne EC2 instance ke sath attach kar rahe ho.
Jaise external hard drive ko dubara plug-in karte ho taake purane files access ho jayein.

---

### ğŸ”¹ **Step 4: Volume Mount Karna (Use Karne Ke Liye Ready Banana)**

```bash
sudo mkdir /data
sudo mount /dev/xvdf /data
```

ğŸ§  Ye step volume ko **mount** karta hai jahan tumhare purane data automatically available ho jata hai.
Ab tum `/data` folder me ja ke files check kar sakte ho â€” sab wapas milenge.

---

### âœ… **Final Note:**

Snapshot lena aur usse restore karna **disaster recovery** ke liye sabse simple aur powerful method hai.
EBS snapshot se tum apna data hamesha safe aur recoverable rakh sakte ho â€” chahe EC2 delete ho ya volume corrupt ho jaye.

